text: Clinical Obstetrics and Gynecology is a quarterly peer-reviewed medical journal covering obstetrics and gynecology. It was established in 1958 and is published by Lippincott Williams & Wilkins. The editor-in-chief is James R. Scott (University of Utah School of Medicine). According to the Journal Citation Reports, the journal has a 2015 impact factor of 1.619, ranking it 51st out of 80 journals in the category "Obstetrics & Gynecology". ==References== ==External links== * Category:Obstetrics and gynaecology journals Category:Lippincott Williams & Wilkins academic journals Category:Publications established in 1958 Category:Quarterly journals Category:English-language journals
